$ SAS programming: variables
@ variable

{ Attributes

  A variables hat the following attributes:
    • name; it identifies the variable (see also → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/variables/automatic)
    • → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/data-types[data type]: Either numeric (default) or character.
    • length (bytes used to store the value the variable referes to)
    • → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/formats-informats[format]
    • → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/formats-informats[informat]
    • A label (description up to 256 characters)
    • The position in an observation
    • Index type (none, simple, composite or both)

}
{ Variable names

}
{ Size of a variable

  By default, SAS creates each variable with a length of 8 bytes - longer character values are
  then truncated.
  
  The → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/statements/length statement can be used to specify a different size.

}
{ Type of a variable

  The → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/data-types[data type] of a variable is either numeric or character.

}
{ Missing values #sas-variables-missing

  → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/variables/missing-values

}

sa:

  → Companies-Products/SAS/programming

  → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/variables/list[variable lists]
